The paper presents a differentiable implementation of the particle filter algorithm for end-to-end learning in state estimation problems. This work involves machine learning (ML) techniques such as optimization and neural networks, which are commonly found in the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also focuses on robotics applications, which suggests the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Additionally, the paper uses computer vision techniques for localization, which suggests the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of algorithmic priors, which is a topic commonly found in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper deals with recursive state estimation, which is a topic commonly found in the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
